# Flutter ViewModel Patterns and Best Practices

## ViewModel Structure
The main ViewModel pattern is demonstrated in [lib/UI/profile/profile_view_model.dart](mdc:lib/UI/profile/profile_view_model.dart)

## Core ViewModel Principles

### 1. State Management
```dart
class ProfilePageViewModel extends ChangeNotifier {
  Profile _profile = Profile();
  Profile get profile => _profile;
  
  bool _isLoading = false;
  bool get isLoading => _isLoading;
  
  // Always notify listeners when state changes
  void _setLoading(bool loading) {
    _isLoading = loading;
    notifyListeners();
  }
}
```

### 2. Loading State Management
Always use try-finally pattern for loading states:
```dart
Future<void> someAsyncOperation() async {
  _isLoading = true;
  notifyListeners();
  
  try {
    // Perform async operation
    await repository.someOperation();
    
    // Update state
    _profile = newProfile;
  } catch (e) {
    // Handle errors
    log("Error: $e");
    // Don't rethrow to avoid breaking UI state
  } finally {
    _isLoading = false; // Always reset loading state
    notifyListeners();
  }
}
```

### 3. Error Handling Strategy
Handle errors gracefully without breaking the UI:
```dart
try {
  await repository.operation();
} catch (e) {
  log("Error during operation: $e");
  // Handle specific error types
  if (e.toString().contains('permission')) {
    // Show permission error
  } else if (e.toString().contains('network')) {
    // Show network error
  }
  // Don't rethrow - maintain UI state
}
```

## Common ViewModel Patterns

### Profile Loading
```dart
Future<Profile> loadProfile() async {
  _isLoading = true;
  notifyListeners();
  
  try {
    final String? userId = _userRepository.getUserId();
    if (userId == null) {
      throw Exception('Benutzer-ID konnte nicht ermittelt werden');
    }
    
    final Profile profile = await _profileRepository.getUserProfileById(userId);
    
    // Load additional data
    final String? email = _userRepository.getUserEmail();
    if (email != null) {
      profile.email = email;
    }
    
    final String? imageUrl = await _profileRepository.getProfileImageUrl(userId);
    if (imageUrl != null) {
      profile.imageUrl = imageUrl;
    }
    
    _profile = profile;
    return profile;
  } finally {
    _isLoading = false;
    notifyListeners();
  }
}
```

### Profile Updates
```dart
Future<void> updateProfile(Profile profile) async {
  _isLoading = true;
  notifyListeners();
  
  try {
    // Handle email updates separately
    final String? currentEmail = _userRepository.getUserEmail();
    if (currentEmail != profile.email && profile.email.isNotEmpty) {
      await _userRepository.updateUserEmail(profile.email);
    }
    
    // Update profile in database
    await _profileRepository.updateUserProfile(profile);
    _profile = profile;
  } catch (e) {
    log("Fehler beim Aktualisieren des Profils: $e");
    // Handle errors gracefully
  } finally {
    _isLoading = false;
    notifyListeners();
  }
}
```

### File Upload with Retry Logic
```dart
Future<void> uploadProfileImage(Uint8List imageBytes, String fileExt) async {
  _isLoading = true;
  notifyListeners();
  
  const int maxRetries = 3;
  
  try {
    final String? userId = _userRepository.getUserId();
    if (userId == null) {
      throw Exception('Benutzer-ID konnte nicht ermittelt werden');
    }
    
    // Validation
    if (imageBytes.isEmpty) {
      throw Exception('Leere Bilddaten - Bildauswahl fehlgeschlagen');
    }
    
    if (imageBytes.length > 10 * 1024 * 1024) {
      throw Exception('Bild zu groß. Maximal 10MB erlaubt.');
    }
    
    // Upload with retry logic
    String? imageUrl;
    Exception? lastException;
    
    for (int attempt = 1; attempt <= maxRetries; attempt++) {
      try {
        imageUrl = await _profileRepository.uploadProfileImage(
          userId, imageBytes, fileExt
        );
        break; // Success
      } catch (e) {
        lastException = e is Exception ? e : Exception(e.toString());
        
        if (attempt < maxRetries && _isRetryableError(e)) {
          await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: attempt * 2));
        } else {
          break;
        }
      }
    }
    
    if (imageUrl == null) {
      throw lastException ?? Exception('Upload fehlgeschlagen nach $maxRetries Versuchen');
    }
    
    // Update profile with new image URL
    _profile.imageUrl = imageUrl;
    await _profileRepository.updateUserProfile(_profile);
    
  } catch (e) {
    log("Upload-Fehler: $e", error: e);
    _handleUploadError(e);
  } finally {
    _isLoading = false;
    notifyListeners();
  }
}
```

## Testing ViewModels

### Test Setup
```dart
setUp(() {
  mockProfileRepository = MockProfileRepository();
  mockUserRepository = MockUserRepository();
  viewModel = ProfilePageViewModel(
    profileRepository: mockProfileRepository,
    userRepository: mockUserRepository,
  );
});
```

### Loading State Tests
```dart
test('should set loading state correctly during operation', () async {
  // Arrange
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
  
  when(mockRepository.operation()).thenAnswer((_) async {
    expect(viewModel.isLoading, true); // Should be loading during operation
    return result;
  });
  
  // Act
  await viewModel.someAsyncOperation();
  
  // Assert
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false); // Should be false after operation
});
```

### Error Handling Tests
```dart
test('should handle errors gracefully', () async {
  // Arrange
  when(mockRepository.operation()).thenThrow(Exception('Error'));
  
  // Act & Assert
  await viewModel.someAsyncOperation(); // Should not throw
  
  // Verify loading state is reset
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
  
  // Verify error handling
  verify(mockRepository.operation()).called(1);
});
```

### Async Operation Tests
```dart
test('should handle async operations correctly', () async {
  // Arrange
  when(mockRepository.operation()).thenAnswer((_) async => result);
  
  // Act
  final result = await viewModel.someAsyncOperation();
  
  // Assert
  expect(result, equals(expectedResult));
  expect(viewModel.isLoading, false);
});
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Always Use try-finally for Loading States
```dart
// ✅ Correct
Future<void> operation() async {
  _isLoading = true;
  notifyListeners();
  try {
    await repository.operation();
  } finally {
    _isLoading = false;
    notifyListeners();
  }
}

// ❌ Avoid
Future<void> operation() async {
  _isLoading = true;
  notifyListeners();
  await repository.operation();
  _isLoading = false; // May not execute if exception occurs
  notifyListeners();
}
```

### 2. Handle Errors Without Breaking UI
```dart
// ✅ Correct
try {
  await operation();
} catch (e) {
  log("Error: $e");
  // Handle error gracefully
} finally {
  _isLoading = false;
  notifyListeners();
}

// ❌ Avoid
try {
  await operation();
} catch (e) {
  rethrow; // This breaks the UI state
} finally {
  _isLoading = false;
  notifyListeners();
}
```

### 3. Use Proper Async/Await
```dart
// ✅ Correct
await viewModel.updateProfile(profile);

// ❌ Avoid
viewModel.updateProfile(profile);
await Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: 100));
```

### 4. Validate Inputs Early
```dart
Future<void> operation(String? userId) async {
  if (userId == null || userId.isEmpty) {
    throw Exception('Invalid user ID');
  }
  
  // Continue with operation
}
```

## Common Anti-Patterns to Avoid

1. **Not resetting loading state**: Always use try-finally
2. **Rethrowing exceptions**: Handle errors gracefully
3. **Manual delays in tests**: Use proper async/await
4. **Missing input validation**: Validate early and often
5. **Forgetting to notify listeners**: Always call notifyListeners() on state changes
6. **Direct service calls in ViewModels**: Use repositories instead
